k": false}, "185592128": {"recommendationid": "185592128", "author": {"steamid": "76561199026456425", "num_games_owned": 150, "num_reviews": 24, "playtime_forever": 539, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 6, "playtime_at_review": 539, "last_played": 1736569406}, "language": "english", "review": "Hearts of Iron III should\u2019ve been amazing. The concept is fantastic, world-spanning strategy, complex diplomacy, and the chance to rewrite history. It had all the potential to be a great experience, especially for fans of grand strategy games. But the reality? It\u2019s a nightmare.\n\nThe bugs are everywhere. Constant crashes, glitches that ruin gameplay, AI that acts like it\u2019s been hit by a truck, and broken save files that make you question why you even bothered. Every time you think you're getting into it, something breaks and pulls you right out of the experience. It\u2019s frustrating as hell. You\u2019ll spend more time fixing issues than actually playing the damn game.\n\nHonestly, save yourself the headache and your money. Hearts of Iron III could have been amazing, but it's just too broken. Instead, go play *Hearts of Iron IV*\u2014it\u2019s everything this game should have been and a thousand times more polished.\n\nRating: 3/10. Don\u2019t waste your time with this mess. Just play HOI4 instead, and save yourself the frustration.", "timestamp_created": 1736876221, "timestamp_updated": 1736876221, "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": "0.476190477609634399", "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}, "185518400": {"recommendationid": "185518400", "author": {"steamid": "76561198062013744", "num_games_owned": 0, "num_reviews": 2, "playtime_forever": 38468, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 1141, "playtime_at_review": 37661, "last_played": 1737395311}, "language": "french", "review": "Jeu bien pens\u00e9 dans l'ensemble mais ne cesse de bu